## Running the server

```sh
go mod tidy
go run .
```

The API listens on port `1337` by default. Use `PORT` to override this:

```sh
PORT=8080 go run .
```

The generated app publishes:

- `/openapi.yaml`
{{#basePathWithoutHost}}
- `{{{basePathWithoutHost}}}/openapi.yaml`
{{/basePathWithoutHost}}
- all paths from the OpenAPI specification

Missing implementations return `501 application/problem+json`.

## Implementing operations

Create a type that implements one of the generated API interfaces and pass it to `NewRouter`:

```go
router := openapi.NewRouter(openapi.ApiHandleFunctions{
	// PetAPI: myPetController,
})
```

The generated `*Controller` types are deliberately stubbed. Replace them or pass your own implementation through `ApiHandleFunctions`.

If an operation has multiple OpenAPI tags, OpenAPI Generator may emit it through multiple API groups. The router registers the first method/path combination and skips later duplicates so the generated app remains startable.
